<center>'''Level 992''', otherwise known as "Epiphany", "Striking Insights" or "Disappointing Realization", is the 993rd level of [[Backrooms Wiki|<span style="background:-webkit-linear-gradient(90deg,black,slategray); -webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent; text-shadow: 0 -1px 2px whitesmoke, 0 -2px 3px black, 0 -5px 20px white, 0 -5px 20px slategray>the Backrooms</span>]].</center>

<div style="background: #3b3b3b70; color: white; border: 15px double #ffffff; box-shadow: 0 0 100px #000000 inset; padding: 1rem; margin:1em; text-shadow: 0 0 10px white, 0 0 10px black; font-size: 16.5px">

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%;"> <div style="position: absolute; width: 100%; height: 100%; float: center; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; overflow: hidden;"><div style="opacity: 0.8;">[[File:Suburb2.jpg|600px|link=]]</div></div> <div style="position: relative; padding: 12px;"><center><span style="font-size:22px; background:-webkit-linear-gradient(90deg,black,slategray); -webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent; text-shadow: 0 -1px 2px whitesmoke, 0 -2px 3px black, 0 -5px 20px white, 0 -5px 20px slategray; font-family: Jost">'''General Description'''</span></center></div></div>
----
{{Blurimage|file=Suburb.webp|caption=An image of Level 992 during the day.}}

'''Level 992''' presents itself as a deserted suburban neighborhood from the early 2000s. Most of the houses on the level seem to be equal in appearance, with hardly any differences, similar windows, subtle color changes, the presence of cars, etc. Many of these houses are also not furnished. Except for occasional cardboard boxes, which may contain personal possessions of people that do not exist, or even furniture. The sky lacks clouds, and the sun never appears, only its light. The sky stays consistent throughout the day; the only change it suffers is the change from blue to black. '''Level 992''' presents layout anomalies, such as houses that overlap, and surreal elements that relate to the dreamcore and weirdcore aesthetic. Roads on this level are awkwardly placed. Occasionally, a road may lead to nowhere, pass directly through a house, or even have a triad of loops that lead to the same place.

Although the suburbs are finite, the roads extend indefinitely into the barren grasslands, with no trees, no clouds, and only dying grass. As one walks deeper into the grass, the sky becomes darker, and the grass dies out.

'''Level 992''' may change from wanderer to wanderer; typically, it takes the architecture, organization, and/or structure out of the wanderers' memories. However, a person who lives in the city or rural areas will experience '''Level 992''' in true form and will not suffer from any changes. These changes are not limited to the appearance of the neighborhood. Weather, or nature, and rarely, one's mentality will be altered by the level. However, these alterations fall short of realism and familiarity. Some examples of this are out-of-place signs and streetlights, inconsistent rain, and unrecognized shapes.

{{Blurimage|file=Suburb2.jpg|caption=Another image of Level 992.}}<div class="marginblock" style="display: inline-flex; width:300px; float:right; clear:right;"></div>

'''Level 992''' is comparable to an ordinary [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] suburban neighborhood in terms of environment. Its temperature averages 18º Celsius (64ª Fahrenheit). Its winds reach about 12 mph, making for a gentle breeze. It has an ordinary day-night cycle, common rain, and an average amount of sunlight. However, '''Level 992''' possesses anomalies that would first go unnoticed: nighttime is slightly longer, rain is oddly noisy, and floods the streets very easily, a misaligned house, a miscolored wall, or something indescribable and strikingly familiar. Wanderers describe the eerie, yet distant feeling of '''Level 992''' to be insurmountable, like they have been there before but cannot remember.

A possible decay in '''Level 992''' has become common talk among discussions related to it. Few wanderers have noticed a gradual decay everywhere in the level, plants dying, metal rusting, dust piling up, walls cracking, and the lights flickering. This decay became popular on [[Backchat (Collaborative Log)|BACK-CHAT]] forums after several posts regarding it went viral. Since then, users have analyzed photos of the level to find any traces of decay. Researchers affirm this decay is nothing short of a myth. However, visitors argue that '''Level 992''' is highly deceptive, and the decay is well-hidden.

<div style="position: relative; width: 100%;"> <div style="position: absolute; width: 100%; height: 100%; float: center; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; overflow: hidden;"><div style="opacity: 0.8;">[[File:Suburb.webp|600px|link=]]</div></div> <div style="position: relative; padding: 12px;"><center><span style="font-size:22px; background:-webkit-linear-gradient(90deg,black,slategray); -webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent; text-shadow: 0 -1px 2px whitesmoke, 0 -2px 3px black, 0 -5px 20px white, 0 -5px 20px slategray; font-family: Jost">'''Epiphanies'''</span></center></div></div>
----
Visions of past memories, although from different perspectives, are dubbed "epiphanies." They manifest randomly anywhere in '''Level 992''', principally through gaps, creeks, and entrances such as doors, cracks, or windows. Epiphanies all seem to have a layer of ambiguity and subjectiveness, but also an odd feeling of hopelessness. They are divided into three main categories: tragic epiphanies, useful epiphanies, and curious epiphanies. Some rarer instances of epiphanies can also be classified under the super-categories of "false epiphanies" and "self-inflicted epiphanies".

{{Blurimage|file=Epiphany.jpg|caption=A regular epiphany manifesting within a mall.}}

Epiphanies are difficult to photograph in full detail. They seem to be hallucinations and can only be seen by a select few people. When an epiphany is photographed, grass hills or a void will be shown in place of it. Strangely enough, these scenarios do not appear as Photoshop-esque still images but rather as real elements of the scenario that interact with other things. They can reflect light and possess depth relative to the place in the photograph. It is possible that epiphanies are manifested as physical places, invisible to the human eye, which showcase the insights.

Tragic epiphanies render past moments of one's life as deceptive, or not what they initially thought they were. That is, the person may have misinterpreted it, or there was something deeper than at first glance. Tragic epiphanies are strikingly obvious. They immerse the traveler in a false world, identical to the real one. As the most common type of epiphany in '''Level 992''', they typically evoke severe depression and grief. A typical example of a tragic epiphany a wanderer could experience is a trusted family member or friend who secretly hates them.

Useful epiphanies showcase more recent memories. Generally, something a wanderer could have done in a situation of risk that would have been quicker and/or more efficient. It is common practice among '''Level 992'''<nowiki/>'s visitors to share advice from useful epiphanies. An example of a useful epiphany would showcase that a foam could have been tossed onto a sink, rather than poured with water, which only makes it grow.

Curious epiphanies enlighten wanderers with scientific and mathematical breakthroughs and wisdom on previously indecipherable mysteries. Curious epiphanies are the rarest and most difficult to crack. Therefore, only the brightest minds can make out what is happening to them.

False epiphanies are deceptive manifestations and are hidden as tragic or curious epiphanies. They display untrue and sometimes unrealistic and/or exaggerated occurrences. At first glance, a false epiphany may be very challenging to recognize. However, they are characterized by small mistakes that can be easily found after closer inspection. These are also somewhat arbitrary and come in an excessive amount of detail.  

Self-inflicted epiphanies are caused by the wanderers themselves and are the second most common type. The level of loneliness leads the wanderer to think about their life, connecting the dots until realizing something deeper is going on. They are the only type of epiphany to not manifest as a visual hallucination or an anomalous location, but rather as a string of thoughts. 

